05/11/2002
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Police on Monday (4 November) released Xhevat Ademi, a leading official of the Albanian National Democratic Party, after detaining him the previous day at the border with Albania.
No details were given about the reasons for the arrest.
Ademi himself would not elaborate on the incident.
In other news, a Macedonian reservist was injured in the leg when a police checkpoint came under fire from unknown assailants in Novo Selo.
A police spokesman reported that a second checkpoint in the north of the country had also been attacked, but there were no casualties.
A police officer was injured in the same area Sunday when he stepped on a mine.
(Dnevnik - 05/11/02;
AP, AFP, Makfax, MIA, A1 TV - 04/11/02)
